{"title_page": "Sandip Ssingh", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{ infobox person\n| name        = Sandip Ssingh\n| alt         = Linesh Bhanushali at a press conference\n| caption     = Sandip Ssingh at a press conference\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1981|09|2}}\n| birth_place      = [[Muzaffarpur]], [[Bihar]], [[India]]\n| death_date  = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| death_place = \n| nationality = Indian\n| years_active  = 2001-present\n| known_for   = [[Mary Kom (film)]], [[Sarbjit (film)|Sarbjit]], [[Bhoomi (film)|Bhoomi]], and [[PM Narendra Modi]]\n| occupation  = Producer, Director of Legend Global Studio\n|homepage={{URL|www.legendglobalstudio.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Sandip Ssingh''' is an Indian [[film maker]]. He started his career as a journalist and later joined Bhansali productions as the CEO. He founded the film production company Legend Global Studio in 2015. Ssingh is known for producing movies like [[Mary Kom (film)]], [[Aligarh (film)|Aligarh]], [[Sarabjit]], [[Bhoomi (film)|Bhoomi]] and ''[[PM Narendra Modi]]''.<ref>https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/modi-biopic-producer-sandip-ssingh-hopeful-for-justice-from-ec-says-even-padmaavat-didnt-face-as-much-stress/articleshow/68902999.cms</ref><ref>https://www.indiatoday.in/programme/countdown-with-rajdeep-sardesai/video/exclusive-pm-narendra-modi-biopic-producer-sandip-ssingh-on-row-1487268-2019-03-26</ref>.\n\n==Early life==\nSsingh was born in [[Muzaffarpur]], [[Bihar]], [[India]], He moved to Mumbai in his early age and completed his education in [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]].\n\n==Career==\nSsingh began his career in 2001 with [[Times Group]] as an entertainment journalist and wrote columns and articles for both [[Bombay Times]] and [[Navbharat Times]]. During this time The Times Group started their own radio channel [[Radio Mirchi]] and Sandip got his first opportunity to be a show producer. He was later appointed as the entertainment head at Radio Mirchi. He joined [[Radio City (Indian radio station)|Radio City]] in 2005 as entertainment head and launched several shows. He moved into [[BIG FM 92.7|BIG FM]] as national entertainment head in 2007<ref>https://www.nagpurtoday.in/roads-in-nagpur-better-than-in-mumbai-asserts-ceo-of-sanjay-leela-bhansali-films/11151654</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9kJWaUMIlyw</ref>\n\nHe produced his first independent show [[Dancing Queen (Indian TV series)|Dancing Queen]] in 2008 on Colors Channel with SOL Entertainment.\n\nHe joined [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]'s production house Bhansali Productions as CEO in 2011. Whilst at Bhansali Productions he co-produced films [[Rowdy Rathore]], [[Shirin Farhad Ki Toh Nikal Padi]], [[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela|Ram Leela]], [[Mary Kom (film)]] and a television series on Star Plus called [[Saraswatichandra (TV series)|Saraswatichandra]] (2013).<ref>http://www.glamsham.com/movies/news/14/oct/10-news-sandeep-singh-sanjay-leela-bhansali-believes-in-rowdy-rathore-kind-of-cinema-101401.asp#</ref>\n \nIn 2015, he launched himself as an independent producer with the critically acclaimed film [[Aligarh]]<ref>https://urbanasian.com/whats-happenin/2015/09/producer-sandeep-singh-pleased-with-the-response-garnered-by-aligarh/</ref> starring [[Manoj Bajpayee]] and [[Rajkumar Rao]]. Oscar nominated film [[Sarbjit (film)|Sarbjit]] in 2016<ref>https://www.spotboye.com/bollywood/Bollywood-interviews/sandeep-singh-omung-and-i-wanted-a-star-who-is-a-performer-hence-it-s-aishwarya-in-sarbjit/573c5a96e98828b615ab5882</ref> starring [[Aishwarya Rai Bachchan]] and [[Randeep Hooda]]. [[Sanjay Dutt]]\u2019s comeback film [[Bhoomi (film)|Bhoomi]] <ref>https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/exclusives/exclusive-bhoomis-producer-sandeep-singh-why-will-sanjay-dutt-do-film-which</ref> in 2017 and a biopic [[PM Narendra Modi]] in 2019 starring [[Vivek Oberoi]].<ref>https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/pm-modi-biopic-to-release-on-april-11-tweets-producer-sandip-ssingh-2018775</ref>\n\n== Filmography & Television ==\n\n===Co Producer===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Co Producer\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Rowdy Rathore]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Shirin Farhad Ki Toh Nikal Padi]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Mary Kom (film)|Mary Kom]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Gabbar Is Back]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|}\n\n===Producer===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Producer\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Aligarh (film)]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Sarbjit (film)|Sarbjit]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Bhoomi (film)|Bhoomi]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[PM Narendra Modi]]''<ref>https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/after-pm-narendra-modi-biopic-gets-stalled-producer-sandip-ssingh-issues-a-statement-heres-what-he-said</ref>\n|{{yes}}\n|}\n\n== Television ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! TV Show\n! Co Producer/ Co Producer\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Dancing Queen (Indian TV series)|Dancing Queen]]''\n|Producer\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Saraswatichandra (TV series)|Saraswatichandra]]''\n|Co Producer\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|5969138}}\n* {{Facebook|Sandipssinghofficial}}\n* {{Instagram|officialsandipssingh}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Sandeep}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Film producers from Mumbai]]\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Undisclosed paid|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n{{ infobox person\n| name        = Sandip Ssingh\n| alt         = Linesh Bhanushali at a press conference\n| caption     = Sandip Ssingh at a press conference\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1981|09|2}}\n| birth_place      = [[Muzaffarpur]], [[Bihar]], [[India]]\n| death_date  = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| death_